[2]
Date: 7 Apr 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Hong Kong - Department of Health [edited]
<http://www.info.gov.hk/dh/new/index.htm>

Situation report on atypical pneumonia 7 Apr 2003
The following is jointly issued by the Department of Health and the
Hospital Authority:
As of 3 PM 7 Apr 2003, an additional 41 patients with symptoms of atypical
pneumonia were admitted to public hospitals. They include 7 healthcare
workers (2 from Princess Margaret Hospital, 4 from Alice Ho Miu Ling
Nethersole Hospital and one from Tuen Mun Hospital) and 10 patients from
Amoy Gardens. The remaining 24 were new patients and contacts of patients
with atypical pneumonia.
A total of 127 patients have recovered from atypical pneumonia and have
been discharged from public hospitals. Of them, 11 were discharged today.
Most of the patients currently in hospital are showing positive responses
to the new treatment protocol. 116 patients are receiving treatment in
intensive care unit.
A 78-year-old female patient died in Queen Elizabeth Hospital last night,
bring to 23 the total number of deaths relating to atypical pneumonia.
The cumulative figure for patients who have been admitted to public
hospitals with atypical pneumonia since 12 Mar 2003 is as follows:
Nature Cumulative No. cases/ Total No. of Discharged cases/ Total No. deaths *
(The numbers in bracket are those with pneumonia symptoms)
Health care workers of Hospitals/Clinics and medical students 208 (208)/ 69/ 23
Patients, family members & visitors 675 (675)/ 58/
Total 883 (883)/ 127
* Most of the deaths occurred in individuals who had a history of chronic
diseases or who sought treatment at a relatively late stage of infection.
